<item>
            <title>[CXF-4307] The inbound Cookie header should be parsed using a semicolon separator by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4307</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The inbound Cookie header may contain something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cookie: a=b;d=c&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the moment the JAX-RS runtime assumes by default that this a single Cookie value, with the last name/value pair recognized and the first one dropped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appears that browsers would more often than not collapse all the Cookies targeted at the specific endpoint into a single header.&lt;br/&gt;
Thus a &apos;;&apos; should be used by default when parsing such headers; this can always be customized... &lt;/p&gt;</description>
